WEBVTT

01:45.523 --> 01:47.900
You should've rang
the doorbell, Brendan.

01:48.109 --> 01:51.445
Hey, you! Yeah, you!
What are you doing?

01:51.654 --> 01:53.739
We found this truck
on the side of the road.

01:53.989 --> 01:57.284
There might be transmission trouble.
You should check it out.

01:57.535 --> 01:59.870
What's going on?
Hey, that's the truck.

02:00.121 --> 02:02.081
The one that was stolen in Newark?

02:02.331 --> 02:03.999
What are you doing with the truck?

02:06.085 --> 02:08.712
It's a gift from Tony Soprano.

02:11.966 --> 02:14.885
Let's call the cops.
Those guys killed Hector.

02:15.094 --> 02:18.931
I don't believe it. We just returned
the biggest score of my year.

02:19.181 --> 02:20.683
Listen, you fuck.

02:20.891 --> 02:24.186
Uncle Junior's breaking Tony's
balls since you hijacked that truck.

02:24.436 --> 02:27.231
You're lucky Tony doesn't shove
the cab up your ass.

02:29.650 --> 02:31.652
What else did Comley say?

02:32.778 --> 02:34.155
Nothing much.

02:34.738 --> 02:36.866
There was stuff missing
from the truck...

02:37.116 --> 02:40.202
...but he didn't give a fuck
as long as the thing's back.

02:40.703 --> 02:44.498
Then he said to tell Tony thanks,
and if Tony needs anything, to call.

02:44.748 --> 02:46.167
Tony?

02:47.251 --> 02:49.170
Those junkie fucks work for Tony.

02:49.378 --> 02:52.590
They hijack Comley's truck,
I get it, and he thanks Tony?

02:53.174 --> 02:58.137
Well, I think you should've taken care
of this Christopher Moltisanti thing...

02:58.387 --> 03:00.639
...the minute it first happened.

03:00.890 --> 03:04.393
You should've sent a clear signal:
"You fuck with Junior Soprano..."

03:04.643 --> 03:07.980
Take it easy.
We're not making a Western here.

03:12.651 --> 03:14.403
Fucking family.

03:14.695 --> 03:17.990
I bought his kid
a $400 surfboard for his birthday.

03:43.682 --> 03:45.476
Mr. Soprano?

03:45.893 --> 03:47.353
How you doing?

03:53.859 --> 03:55.527
Is that a trick picture out there?

03:57.196 --> 03:58.239
Which?

03:58.447 --> 03:59.657
The barn.

04:00.532 --> 04:03.410
And the old tree
all rotted out inside.

04:04.078 --> 04:06.747
It's just a picture I bought.

04:06.956 --> 04:10.000
I remember, in a little gallery
in Provincetown.

04:10.209 --> 04:13.420
That is a special-made
psychological picture.

04:13.629 --> 04:16.382
Like that what-do-you-call-it test.

04:18.467 --> 04:20.094
The Korschach.

04:20.886 --> 04:22.346
You think I want to trick you?

04:22.554 --> 04:24.848
- Oh, no.
- What does that picture say?

04:25.057 --> 04:27.601
"We're from Harvard,
and what do you think of...

04:27.810 --> 04:31.021
...this depressing barn
and this rotted-out tree here?"

04:31.522 --> 04:33.399
It's depressing and scary to you?

04:33.607 --> 04:35.109
Not to me.

04:35.401 --> 04:38.112
But it's got that built right into it.

04:39.697 --> 04:40.823
How are things?

04:41.031 --> 04:42.408
Good.

04:43.325 --> 04:45.119
I had a real good week.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.497
A friend's in the hospital.

04:48.747 --> 04:50.749
That's never pleasant, but...

04:51.375 --> 04:53.544
Otherwise, I'm having a good week.

04:53.752 --> 04:56.213
- What's he in for?
- They thought it was an ulcer.

04:56.422 --> 04:58.299
You know, then this, then that.

04:58.507 --> 05:00.509
- You're worried about him?
- Jackie?

05:00.718 --> 05:04.054
Jackie's so fucking mean,
he'll scare that cancer away.

05:04.471 --> 05:06.098
Your friend has cancer?

05:09.810 --> 05:13.314
Jackie, when they hook you up,
do you make sure they don't have...

05:13.564 --> 05:15.899
...air in your veins,
or is that just bullshit?

05:16.108 --> 05:17.234
What do you mean?

05:17.484 --> 05:21.864
This is a good hospital, sweetheart.
Nothing like that's gonna happen here.

05:22.114 --> 05:25.367
Air in the line'll kill you.
You know who else...?

05:25.576 --> 05:26.618
Hey!

05:27.828 --> 05:29.747
You know who else has cancer?

05:30.164 --> 05:32.041
Tommy DiPalma.

05:32.666 --> 05:35.419
He's got it much worse.
It's eating his brain away.

05:35.669 --> 05:38.005
Hey, somebody having a baby or what?

05:38.881 --> 05:40.632
- How you doing?
- All right.

05:40.883 --> 05:42.509
- How you feeling?
- Good.

05:42.760 --> 05:45.012
Hesh, how you doing?
Good to see you.

05:45.262 --> 05:46.847
Thanks for coming.

05:47.139 --> 05:49.058
Jackie, looking well, pal.

05:49.266 --> 05:50.642
Here, Ro, for you.

05:51.101 --> 05:52.561
You're beautiful.

05:53.729 --> 05:56.398
Mikey, nice to see you again
in men's clothing.

05:56.607 --> 05:58.650
I should grab a fire extinguisher.

05:59.109 --> 06:03.322
I heard your friend had a spontaneous
combustion in his restaurant.

06:03.572 --> 06:06.033
I'm going to the cafeteria.
Want anything?

06:06.283 --> 06:07.576
A plate of <i>braciole.</i>

06:09.328 --> 06:12.206
- They got grappa in this thing?
- Oh, I wish.

06:12.456 --> 06:14.875
See you later. I got some errands.

06:15.292 --> 06:17.711
- Give Junior my love.
- I will.

06:18.587 --> 06:19.588
Hey.

06:19.755 --> 06:23.801
Tell my uncle I sent back the truck.
Give me the vinegar peppers he owes me.

06:28.180 --> 06:29.723
Thank God he left.

06:29.973 --> 06:32.643
He's a nice guy,
but he's like the Grim Reaper.

06:32.893 --> 06:36.522
He knows every guy with cancer,
and he can't wait to tell you.

06:36.772 --> 06:40.150
Jackie, you might be a candidate
for clinical trials.

06:40.401 --> 06:42.528
These stem cell therapies...

06:42.778 --> 06:46.156
Paulie, he don't want to hear
no more cancer talk.

06:46.365 --> 06:48.075
Get the fuck out of here!

06:48.283 --> 06:53.122
Trust me, you caught a break being
Jewish. See what I gotta deal with?

06:53.580 --> 06:56.125
Jews, that's right.
I knew there was something.

06:56.375 --> 06:58.085
Tony, you know Teittleman?

06:58.293 --> 07:01.713
Owns property. Owns the motel
down the street from the club.

07:02.506 --> 07:05.175
The Jew with the black clothes
and the curls.

07:05.384 --> 07:06.927
They're called Hasidim.

07:07.177 --> 07:08.804
"Hasidim" but I don't believe them.

07:09.847 --> 07:12.933
- What does Teittleman want?
- A divorce for his daughter.

07:13.142 --> 07:14.435
What do you mean?

07:14.685 --> 07:18.105
His son-in-law will not give
his daughter the consent...

07:18.355 --> 07:21.442
...unless Teittleman gives him
50% of his motel.

07:21.650 --> 07:23.527
They call it a <i>get.</i>

07:23.735 --> 07:25.446
Why don't he just...?

07:25.654 --> 07:28.490
It's taboo for their religion.

07:28.699 --> 07:30.075
You know about this shit?

07:30.325 --> 07:34.413
Run. Trust me. You don't want
to do business with these people.

07:34.621 --> 07:37.958
He said there's 25 large in it
if we can get him this <i>get.</i>

07:38.167 --> 07:39.501
There's a saying amongst Jews:

07:39.751 --> 07:42.796
"When a Jew gets a divorce,
even the altar sheds tears."

07:43.046 --> 07:44.840
All right, I heard enough.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.759
Look, I'm getting kind of tired.

07:49.011 --> 07:50.804
Let's go get a cup of coffee.

07:51.346 --> 07:53.515
See you later, Jackie.
Take care.

08:20.083 --> 08:22.878
That crash was Meadow Soprano
jumping her cue.

08:23.086 --> 08:27.674
Miss Marris, we're exhausted from
studying for SATs. We were up past 2.

08:27.883 --> 08:29.927
- Are you her lawyer?
- No.

08:30.177 --> 08:32.554
Why they'd schedule SATs
the same week...

08:32.763 --> 08:34.723
- Same day.
- What?

08:37.518 --> 08:41.313
If we're kicked out of Concert Singers,
we lose our best extracurricular.

08:41.563 --> 08:44.107
Goodbye, Berkeley.
Hello, Glassboro State.

08:44.316 --> 08:49.321
I cannot wait until all of North America
is between me and Tony and Carmela.

08:49.530 --> 08:50.822
New Jersey blows.

08:51.073 --> 08:53.116
I want to go to Berkeley so bad.

08:53.367 --> 08:55.494
The whole East, I can't deal anymore.

08:55.744 --> 08:58.080
So we don't sleep till after the SATs.

08:58.330 --> 09:00.999
Don't mind the mess.
I wasn't expecting company.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.293
I couldn't wait.
I had to see the new house.

09:03.502 --> 09:06.421
- Where's King Arthur?
- Downstairs. This plumbing!

09:06.630 --> 09:08.090
- Here?
- Yeah.

09:10.050 --> 09:13.095
Oh, I love the coziness.

09:14.012 --> 09:16.014
Welcome to the neighborhood.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.976
Well, the school district, anyway.

09:19.226 --> 09:21.853
Carm, you did not have to do this.

09:22.604 --> 09:25.774
I mean, we don't see each other
like we used to...

09:25.983 --> 09:28.110
I want that to change.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.283
- Could this be Artie Bucco?
- Hey, <i>capitano!</i>

09:34.491 --> 09:35.826
The place looks good.

09:36.034 --> 09:38.579
It needs a little work,
but we'll get there.

09:38.787 --> 09:42.583
You need some cash until the
insurance on the restaurant comes...

09:42.791 --> 09:47.337
There'll be an Italian president
before I see any insurance money.

09:47.588 --> 09:49.214
I thought that was settled.

09:49.464 --> 09:52.759
Join the club. They're doing
a second arson investigation.

09:52.968 --> 09:55.470
They think you're Mobbed up?
You're a working stiff.

09:55.721 --> 10:00.642
It doesn't make any sense. Who would
burn down a perfectly good restaurant?

10:01.518 --> 10:02.936
It's stupid.

10:03.937 --> 10:05.230
Insane.

10:08.609 --> 10:11.194
- Sorry, Artie.
- Life goes on, no?

10:11.528 --> 10:13.363
I could always be a plumber, no?

10:13.572 --> 10:15.907
Only one concept to master:
Shit runs downhill.

10:16.158 --> 10:20.120
Yes, it does. Come in the kitchen.
I'll buy you a beer.

10:33.258 --> 10:34.426
- Mr. Soprano.
- Mr. Teittleman.

10:34.635 --> 10:36.345
- My pleasure.
- Have a seat.

10:36.595 --> 10:38.805
- Thank you.
- Silvio you know.

10:39.056 --> 10:40.515
Paulie.

10:40.766 --> 10:42.017
How are you?

10:42.309 --> 10:44.019
This is my son.

10:45.562 --> 10:47.481
Does he have a name?

10:47.689 --> 10:49.733
Oh, I'm sorry. It's Hillel.

10:52.361 --> 10:54.988
You know about
my daughter and her husband?

10:55.238 --> 10:56.490
Yeah, he knows.

10:56.698 --> 10:58.408
Do you have a daughter, Mr. Soprano?

10:58.659 --> 11:01.495
Yes. Call me Tony.

11:01.703 --> 11:04.873
What would you do if she was
abused by her husband?

11:05.123 --> 11:06.166
Talk to him.

11:06.375 --> 11:08.293
Yeah, in ball-peen hammer.

11:08.502 --> 11:10.170
I think you understand my anger.

11:10.671 --> 11:14.508
He's harming my daughter,
and he's mocking our laws of marriage.

11:14.716 --> 11:18.261
Look, let's understand each other
from the get-go here, okay?

11:18.512 --> 11:20.138
I'm in waste management.

11:20.389 --> 11:24.309
I'm only here because I'm Silvio's
friend, you're Silvio's friend.

11:24.518 --> 11:27.270
You may be having a problem
I can help you with.

11:27.521 --> 11:29.815
If I can do it,
that will make me happy.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.024
Ha!

11:31.191 --> 11:32.818
What's your problem, Hil?

11:43.495 --> 11:44.746
Please finish.

11:44.955 --> 11:47.541
You're being shaken down
for 50% of your motels.

11:47.749 --> 11:48.750
Correct.

11:48.917 --> 11:53.046
The goon squads who smacked these
husbands around to get the divorce...

11:53.255 --> 11:55.090
...were put out of business
by the D.A.

11:56.925 --> 12:00.345
All right, 25%.
He wants 50, we get 25.

12:00.595 --> 12:02.055
I don't understand.

12:02.264 --> 12:03.682
I'm not talking to you.

12:14.151 --> 12:18.113
You get me what I want, Mr. Soprano,
and you have a deal.

12:18.321 --> 12:19.531
It's done.

12:21.616 --> 12:24.119
You let them in our motel,
you'll never get them out.

12:25.120 --> 12:27.414
That's a commercial, isn't it?

12:34.796 --> 12:38.300
Julio, before lunch
I want you to do bedding inventory.

12:38.550 --> 12:41.428
Half-hour, and no <i>cervezas,</i> please.

12:45.974 --> 12:47.517
Yes, may I help you?

12:47.768 --> 12:49.978
That depends. Are you Ariel?

12:50.228 --> 12:52.981
That also depends.
Are you a bill collector?

12:53.190 --> 12:56.151
What is this, the Catskills?
Shecky Greene we got here.

12:56.401 --> 12:58.153
Let's talk about your father-in-law.

12:58.361 --> 12:59.988
I'm sorry. He's not here.

13:00.238 --> 13:02.199
We know he's not here.

13:02.449 --> 13:06.703
But we want to talk to you
about him and you. And him.

13:06.953 --> 13:08.955
This problem that you're having.

13:09.206 --> 13:11.082
Look, I don't know who you are...

13:11.333 --> 13:15.837
...but any problem I may be having
with my family is none of your matter.

13:16.087 --> 13:17.339
So get out of here.

13:18.089 --> 13:20.801
No, no, look.
Shlomo is a friend of mine.

13:21.009 --> 13:22.511
And you're bragging this?

13:23.929 --> 13:24.971
This guy...

13:25.180 --> 13:28.350
You couldn't possibly understand
what's going on here.

13:28.975 --> 13:32.771
Shlomo is an arrogant,
ignorant control freak.

13:33.021 --> 13:37.275
Look, I know him since before I had
hair on my <i>pitzl</i>. I made this place.

13:37.776 --> 13:41.279
The flyers, the car rental drop-off,
the business breakfast.

13:41.488 --> 13:43.198
It was me, not him.

13:43.448 --> 13:46.535
So I sweated blood into this place,
and he owes me.

13:46.785 --> 13:49.120
And I intend to get what's mine.

13:49.329 --> 13:53.166
So, please, don't embarrass yourself
any further. Just leave.

13:53.375 --> 13:56.127
I'm not embarrassed. You embarrassed?

13:57.420 --> 13:59.047
Listen to me, you weirdo fuck.

13:59.297 --> 14:03.218
You give Shlomo whatever he wants
and you forget this 50% shit.

14:03.468 --> 14:06.555
You got nothing coming to you.
Understand me? Nothing!

14:06.805 --> 14:08.014
Fuck you!

14:08.265 --> 14:10.809
<i>Bupkes</i>. Say <i>bupkes,</i> Paulie.

14:11.059 --> 14:12.769
That's how they say "nothing."

14:14.187 --> 14:16.356
Fuck that.
This is how I say "nothing."

14:17.983 --> 14:19.442
How's that for nothing?

14:22.821 --> 14:25.282
- You know what?
- Probably not.

14:25.490 --> 14:27.367
The fundraiser for Pediatric Hospital?

14:27.617 --> 14:30.912
I'm gonna hire Artie and Charmaine
to cater it.

14:32.831 --> 14:36.084
Since when do we
open our house to strangers?

14:36.293 --> 14:39.254
Oh, you're right.
Let's just move back to Italy.

14:39.462 --> 14:43.550
We'll live in a hill town like
our ancestors, put a wall around it...

14:43.758 --> 14:46.761
...and throw burning oil on all
travelers that knock at the gate.

14:48.305 --> 14:50.098
Come on!

14:52.475 --> 14:57.230
Poor Charmaine. I tried to find
nice things to say about that house.

14:57.480 --> 15:00.817
Ain't that bad. Just needs
a little work, that's all.

15:01.026 --> 15:04.362
Those two are so broke.
And that fire.

15:05.405 --> 15:07.490
If that insurance would
get off its ass.

15:07.699 --> 15:10.243
- Could it have been arson?
- What's the matter with you?

15:14.080 --> 15:15.749
Hey!

15:18.126 --> 15:21.171
I can't believe you guys
didn't get enough for us.

15:22.297 --> 15:23.673
Yeah, put Matt on.

15:25.008 --> 15:26.009
Hold on.

15:26.176 --> 15:28.929
What's going on?
You trying to damage your inner ears?

15:29.179 --> 15:30.388
We're studying.

15:30.639 --> 15:33.141
These are practice tests
and they're brutal.

15:33.350 --> 15:35.393
Your parents know you're here,
<i>cacciatore?</i>

15:35.602 --> 15:37.729
- They don't care.
- She's sleeping over.

15:40.857 --> 15:43.109
Can Hunter please sleep over?

15:43.318 --> 15:45.946
Start sleeping, then.
Study time's over.

15:46.154 --> 15:48.239
We still have six more chapters left.

15:49.699 --> 15:54.120
Then can you keep the decibel level
down, please? For my husband.

15:57.540 --> 16:00.001
Matt, I'm serious, you guys.

16:00.251 --> 16:02.712
If we can't score some crystal,
we're dead.

16:02.921 --> 16:06.633
With this budget, we can do
three waiters for the hors d'oeuvres...

16:06.883 --> 16:08.343
...two for the champagne.

16:08.593 --> 16:12.514
It's such a load off.
This party has me at sixes and sevens.

16:12.764 --> 16:15.809
Pediatric Hospital's
such a worthy cause.

16:16.101 --> 16:17.102
Oona!

16:19.521 --> 16:24.025
There's fingerprints on the breakfront.
I want this place to sparkle.

16:26.820 --> 16:29.489
She's usually very good. From Poland.

16:31.074 --> 16:33.451
<i>Please get in the car, sir.</i>

16:33.785 --> 16:38.540
Like the cop would be calling him
"sir" if the cameras weren't around.

16:39.457 --> 16:40.500
I saw this one.

16:40.709 --> 16:43.253
Then call Tony
so he can call Junior...

16:43.503 --> 16:45.672
...and see if we can
change the channel.

16:45.880 --> 16:47.590
Get that, will you, babe?

16:47.799 --> 16:50.260
Sure. I'm the only one
who has to go to work.

16:50.510 --> 16:53.054
Yeah, restaurant hostess.
Real tough work.

16:53.304 --> 16:55.015
It's your little cousin.

16:56.516 --> 16:57.892
- What's up?
- How are you?

16:58.101 --> 17:00.228
- What are you doing here?
- Hello to you too.

17:00.437 --> 17:02.022
Hunter, what are you doing?

17:02.272 --> 17:04.733
Don't mind him. His brain is fried.

17:04.983 --> 17:06.526
You want a soda or something?

17:06.776 --> 17:08.862
- How about a beer?
- Yeah, right.

17:09.112 --> 17:12.198
Just kidding. I'll have a Coke
if you have one.

17:12.407 --> 17:13.783
What do you want, Meadow?

17:14.034 --> 17:15.827
She wants something from me.

17:16.036 --> 17:17.579
In your dreams, Brendan.

17:18.455 --> 17:20.206
So, what do you want?

17:22.959 --> 17:24.419
I wanna cop.

17:26.963 --> 17:28.173
Here you go.

17:29.382 --> 17:30.717
What do you mean, "cop"?

17:30.967 --> 17:33.261
Score. We want to score some crystal.

17:33.470 --> 17:34.554
You got money?

17:34.763 --> 17:37.015
- You ain't giving them shit.
- Why not?

17:37.223 --> 17:39.934
Your father'll put a bullet
in my head.

17:40.852 --> 17:42.896
Since when do you take speed, anyway?

17:43.104 --> 17:45.106
She doesn't. I need it to study.

17:45.356 --> 17:48.401
Yeah, right. Hunter needs it.

17:48.651 --> 17:51.071
Forget about it. No fucking way.

17:53.865 --> 17:54.991
What?

17:55.200 --> 17:56.910
He just craves attention.

17:59.120 --> 18:02.624
Just thought I'd ask you
before we went to Jefferson Avenue.

18:02.832 --> 18:06.586
Those <i>melanzane</i> will rob you,
rape you and leave you on the road.

18:08.713 --> 18:10.090
What do you see in him?

18:10.924 --> 18:12.926
Money. What do you think?

18:13.176 --> 18:14.385
Fuck you.

18:14.636 --> 18:16.888
- See you, Christopher.
- I got my own money.

18:17.138 --> 18:19.933
What about me?
Nobody's gonna say goodbye to me?

18:22.894 --> 18:23.895
Bye.

18:24.104 --> 18:26.648
- Bye.
- Bye, guys.

18:30.568 --> 18:33.988
You can't let her go to Jefferson
Avenue. They'll sell her Ajax.

18:34.197 --> 18:37.659
She won't go there. She just wants
me to give her some speed.

18:37.867 --> 18:41.496
Isn't it better if she gets it from you
with all that poison around?

18:43.123 --> 18:46.251
Kids. You think you can protect them.

18:46.835 --> 18:48.461
But you can't.

18:49.295 --> 18:53.091
<i>With the rainy season,
chicks alter their eating habits.</i>

18:53.341 --> 18:55.677
Are you watching
that nature shit again?

18:55.927 --> 18:57.220
What are you doing here?

18:57.470 --> 18:59.931
My kid stepped on a nail.
I had to get him a shot.

19:00.140 --> 19:01.641
Yeah, where is he?

19:01.891 --> 19:03.226
At the ER with Carmela.

19:03.643 --> 19:06.396
So whatever happened
with the Jew at the motel?

19:06.646 --> 19:09.232
They reached out to him,
he wasn't receptive.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.151
They're going back.

19:15.113 --> 19:18.408
- Want me to leave?
- Just looking for my nurse's pen.

19:18.658 --> 19:21.870
You got the wrong room
because you are not my nurse.

19:22.120 --> 19:23.913
I know, but I made up the bed.

19:24.122 --> 19:27.458
No, sweetheart. I have not been
out of this bed all day.

19:28.459 --> 19:32.172
- Sorry, I need to check some vitals...
- What are you doing?

19:32.422 --> 19:34.132
That seems to be working fine.

19:34.382 --> 19:37.302
Nobody sends flower arrangements
like New York.

19:37.552 --> 19:39.304
Let me just check his...

19:40.054 --> 19:41.222
Oh!

19:43.558 --> 19:45.018
This damn IV.

19:45.685 --> 19:46.978
Damn!

19:47.312 --> 19:48.730
I got it.

19:53.902 --> 19:58.114
I seem to be having a problem. Do you
mind if I borrow one of your gowns?

19:59.616 --> 20:01.326
It's okay.
It's a private party.

20:02.744 --> 20:06.623
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.
Have a nice night.

20:07.081 --> 20:08.082
Oh, <i>Madonna!</i>

20:16.549 --> 20:21.221
I got you, you prick!
You should've seen your face!

20:21.429 --> 20:24.182
- You prick!
- "I haven't been out of bed."

20:25.058 --> 20:26.100
Look at your face.

20:26.309 --> 20:27.560
Who the hell is this?

20:28.353 --> 20:33.149
Relax, Mr. Aprile.
It's time for your sponge bath.

20:37.946 --> 20:41.491
She's a friend of mine
from the club. Nice girl.

20:42.951 --> 20:45.870
I joined them later on.
We got a little booze.

20:48.957 --> 20:51.668
You were nice to have a party
for your friend.

20:52.210 --> 20:53.378
Yeah.

20:59.717 --> 21:01.261
"Tufts Medical School."

21:06.140 --> 21:07.558
You're a doctor.

21:08.101 --> 21:10.979
What do you think? About Jackie?

21:11.896 --> 21:14.023
I'd have to know more about
his condition.

21:14.232 --> 21:16.776
I told you about his condition.
He's got cancer.

21:17.026 --> 21:18.403
What kind of cancer?

21:18.653 --> 21:20.071
It's in the intestines.

21:21.197 --> 21:24.200
There was a tumor
and they took it out.

21:25.159 --> 21:26.786
And it's recurred.

21:26.995 --> 21:30.039
But you said he might go home.
They're not operating?

21:31.833 --> 21:33.376
It's next to something vital.

21:33.584 --> 21:35.837
- I see.
- You see?

21:36.045 --> 21:38.089
From what you're saying,
it doesn't sound good.

21:38.298 --> 21:39.882
From what I'm saying?

21:40.091 --> 21:42.176
What do I know? I'm not a doctor.

21:42.427 --> 21:44.512
- You're angry. Who with?
- I'll tell you.

21:45.555 --> 21:48.558
This man has had chemo every day
for three weeks.

21:48.808 --> 21:51.185
He still has every last hair
on his head.

21:51.436 --> 21:55.148
Every last hair on his head,
and he's got a beautiful head of hair.

21:55.398 --> 21:58.151
So don't tell me how it sounds.
You don't know him or me...

21:58.401 --> 22:00.028
...or what you're talking about.

22:00.278 --> 22:03.489
We're getting closer to you
confronting your true feelings...

22:03.740 --> 22:05.658
...about what's really going on.

22:05.867 --> 22:08.494
Wait a minute.
I just told you my true feelings.

22:08.745 --> 22:10.663
You tell me what's really going on.

22:10.872 --> 22:13.666
The tree in the painting rotted out,
you said.

22:13.875 --> 22:15.752
Nothing indicates that.

22:16.002 --> 22:18.296
I knew that was a fucking scam.

22:18.546 --> 22:21.299
I knew that painting was
a fucking scam!

22:21.549 --> 22:24.677
You remember your dream? The ducks?

22:25.303 --> 22:27.221
It took on another meaning.

22:28.514 --> 22:30.725
What happens to a tree
that's rotted out?

22:30.933 --> 22:33.186
Trees, ducks.
What are you? Ranger Rick?

22:33.770 --> 22:36.606
Some job you shrinks got.
You think everybody's lying...

22:36.814 --> 22:40.568
...while you're pulling scams on them!
Fuck you!

22:43.529 --> 22:47.700
There's 37 definites.
We got another 13 maybes...

22:47.950 --> 22:50.578
...plus the whole
Pediatric Hospital Board.

22:51.412 --> 22:52.455
Right.

22:52.663 --> 22:55.166
Are you sure we ordered
enough champagne?

22:56.209 --> 22:57.460
Right.

22:57.919 --> 23:00.838
Gene says they shouldn't be too sober
for the auction.

23:01.089 --> 23:04.342
If anyone ever finds out
you got this from me...

23:04.592 --> 23:07.470
Look at me. This is no joke.

23:07.720 --> 23:11.015
We don't always get along,
but you don't want to see me dead.

23:11.224 --> 23:13.142
I gotta call Hunter.
You're the best.

23:13.393 --> 23:17.522
Hey, I'm serious. Just this once,
okay? I'm no drug dealer.

23:17.772 --> 23:21.359
I don't want to see you get poisoned.
Your father ever finds out...

23:21.609 --> 23:23.736
God, doesn't anyone ever knock?

23:24.445 --> 23:27.532
Tell Brendan that Hunter would
rather die than go out with him.

23:27.782 --> 23:29.158
Brendan?

23:29.534 --> 23:32.412
Christopher, keep that asshole
away from that child.

23:32.662 --> 23:34.997
He asked me to do him a favor,
I did it.

23:35.248 --> 23:38.751
All right, you delivered the message.
Now let Meadow study.

23:44.006 --> 23:46.050
Two <i>goombahs</i>
from the old neighborhood.

23:46.259 --> 23:50.763
What, they think they're gonna name it
the Soprano Wing in the new hospital?

23:51.013 --> 23:53.474
I think you're just
jealous of their money.

23:53.724 --> 23:55.143
- Me?
- Yeah.

23:55.351 --> 23:57.145
Okay, but explain to me this.

23:57.395 --> 24:00.481
He offers us two tickets to the
Caribbean out of friendship.

24:00.731 --> 24:02.358
You say no, they're tainted.

24:02.608 --> 24:05.736
But for some party,
I take his money to clean his toilets.

24:05.945 --> 24:10.074
First of all, Arthur, this is
a paying job and not some cruise.

24:10.324 --> 24:12.743
And why do you always
have to exaggerate?

24:12.952 --> 24:14.954
You're not cleaning his toilets.
You're a chef.

24:15.746 --> 24:19.709
Good. So you don't mind that he
fronts me money for a new place...

24:19.917 --> 24:21.544
...because he offered.

24:23.588 --> 24:24.672
Look at that face.

24:24.881 --> 24:28.718
Oh, God, don't tell me that you
took money from Tony Soprano.

24:28.926 --> 24:33.097
How is it different?
I'm a chef. I need a place to cook.

24:33.347 --> 24:36.309
How? I'm giving Carmela my support,
that's how.

24:36.517 --> 24:38.769
And it's for a very reputable cause.

24:39.312 --> 24:43.191
But to have that man as a partner,
trust me, that would be insane.

24:43.441 --> 24:45.318
It'd mean the end of everything.

24:45.526 --> 24:47.069
At least he made the gesture.

24:47.320 --> 24:51.115
Name me another person who offered us
anything except the Sopranos?

24:51.574 --> 24:54.660
Watch what you're doing.
You're squeezing the quail.

25:02.126 --> 25:03.836
Should we turn on the air?

25:04.045 --> 25:06.255
It's going okay.
Do you like the food?

25:06.506 --> 25:09.383
I was so busy schmoozing,
I barely had a bite.

25:09.634 --> 25:12.178
Don't miss those
little veal <i>tonnatos.</i>

25:12.386 --> 25:13.846
Charmaine!

25:14.222 --> 25:15.223
Sure. Wow.

25:15.473 --> 25:16.557
Charmaine!

25:24.774 --> 25:27.026
Not in the car! Please!
Not in the car!

25:27.276 --> 25:28.903
Shut up! Shut up!

25:29.153 --> 25:31.322
Shut up and get in
the fucking car!

25:32.031 --> 25:35.326
Get in there, you miserable
fucking prick!

25:43.125 --> 25:45.169
I can't get used to
strangers in my house.

25:45.419 --> 25:46.504
Why'd you invite them?

25:50.716 --> 25:52.009
Try one of these.

25:56.138 --> 25:57.723
You're a fucking great cook.

25:58.474 --> 26:00.351
I cook like this...

26:01.811 --> 26:03.563
...it reminds me of what I lost.

26:04.981 --> 26:08.901
To have my restaurant ripped from me.
I can't tell you...

26:09.151 --> 26:10.778
It was like losing a limb.

26:13.364 --> 26:16.200
- Sometimes I lay in bed...
<i>- Statti zitto!</i> Enough already.

26:16.450 --> 26:18.911
Forget about the past.
Look to the future.

26:19.161 --> 26:23.291
I'm sick of hearing of your restaurant.
Shut up, you depressing jerk!

26:23.541 --> 26:25.585
What the fuck do you know about it?

26:28.170 --> 26:29.589
You motherfucker.

26:37.847 --> 26:39.599
You fucking jerk!

26:40.266 --> 26:42.268
Come on. Give it up.

26:47.356 --> 26:49.025
See what you get when you...

26:51.485 --> 26:52.987
Fucking son of a bitch!

26:54.905 --> 26:57.283
- Get up, you stubborn fuck.
- Please!

26:57.491 --> 27:01.078
Too late. All this because
you won't say yes to a divorce?

27:01.329 --> 27:02.455
It's not that simple!

27:02.997 --> 27:06.584
Why not? You sign your fucking name
to a piece of paper!

27:06.834 --> 27:08.252
I don't like you.

27:08.502 --> 27:11.339
Well, I don't like you.
You believe this prick?

27:11.756 --> 27:15.551
What do I get, huh? You work
for nothing? I don't think so!

27:15.760 --> 27:17.970
I say we force-feed him his sombrero.

27:18.179 --> 27:21.265
She wants to go to Israel,
I send her. I pay.

27:21.515 --> 27:24.435
I feed her, I clothe her,
I put a roof over her head.

27:24.685 --> 27:27.772
I worked for her father for 20 years
and took his abuse.

27:28.022 --> 27:29.315
So I get nothing?

27:29.523 --> 27:31.317
- Stand up!
- We don't care.

27:31.567 --> 27:33.694
Tough fucking luck, ain't it, pal?

27:34.904 --> 27:36.656
You mother...!

27:37.907 --> 27:38.949
Silvio!

27:44.497 --> 27:46.290
Motherfucker.

27:46.582 --> 27:48.376
This guy's a bull.

27:49.418 --> 27:52.630
Paulie, if we don't kill this prick...

27:53.130 --> 27:54.882
...we should put him to work.

28:00.763 --> 28:02.223
Time's a-wasting.

28:02.473 --> 28:05.685
I was lucky I could get out at all
with that party tonight.

28:10.523 --> 28:11.565
Shit!

28:18.614 --> 28:21.033
- Hello.
<i>- Tony.</i>

28:21.242 --> 28:24.787
Sorry to bother you.
This isn't working out how we hoped.

28:24.995 --> 28:27.581
<i>With our friend
with the funny sideburns.</i>

28:27.832 --> 28:29.875
Don't say no more on the phone.

28:31.001 --> 28:32.795
I'm coming down.

28:33.504 --> 28:35.089
Shit!

28:36.090 --> 28:37.591
I gotta go.

28:39.969 --> 28:41.095
You just got here.

28:41.303 --> 28:43.639
Yeah, I know, but I gotta go.

28:56.569 --> 28:58.654
What's that painting mean to you?

29:00.614 --> 29:04.076
Nothing. It just reminds me
of David Hockey.

29:23.262 --> 29:25.139
You want something to munch on?

29:26.599 --> 29:27.933
Are you kidding me?

29:28.142 --> 29:31.520
Most guys I know would be happy
to get rid of their wife.

29:32.062 --> 29:34.148
I tried explaining the realities here.

29:34.398 --> 29:37.067
This guy's as stubborn
as a fucking mule.

29:37.276 --> 29:39.111
He says it's principle.

29:39.403 --> 29:43.324
I think we gotta... you know.
That's why we called you.

29:43.741 --> 29:45.618
I promised the father-in-law
I wouldn't.

29:45.826 --> 29:47.453
I don't know what else to do.

29:52.875 --> 29:54.877
You're a stupid fucker,
you know that?

29:55.419 --> 29:56.879
I've heard it said.

29:57.087 --> 29:58.839
What are you, proud of it?

29:59.423 --> 30:03.969
You kill me and a dark cloud goes over
Shlomo's house.

30:04.220 --> 30:08.098
Either way, they'll be no <i>get</i>
unless restitution is made.

30:08.974 --> 30:12.061
You really would let me kill you,
you sick fuck.

30:14.522 --> 30:16.357
You ever heard of the Masada?

30:17.691 --> 30:21.612
For two years, 900 Jews
held their own...

30:21.821 --> 30:24.865
...against 15,000 Roman soldiers.

30:26.075 --> 30:28.994
They chose death before enslavement.

30:29.453 --> 30:32.665
And the Romans, where are they now?

30:33.833 --> 30:36.126
You're looking at them, asshole.

30:40.506 --> 30:44.385
Yea, though I walk through
the valley of the shadow of death...

30:44.635 --> 30:47.346
...I fear no evil
for Thou art with me.

30:47.596 --> 30:49.390
Yeah, hold that thought.

31:01.402 --> 31:02.403
Yeah?

31:02.570 --> 31:06.615
I'm with my non-shellfish-eating
friend, and I'm tapped out.

31:06.866 --> 31:08.784
This guy won't listen to reason.

31:10.452 --> 31:11.954
Didn't I tell you, huh?

31:12.204 --> 31:14.248
I warned you to keep away
from them.

31:14.498 --> 31:15.916
He left me no options.

31:16.166 --> 31:18.586
He's willing to go down with the ship.

31:20.671 --> 31:22.131
Here's a thought.

31:22.506 --> 31:24.842
Maybe he's willing to go to
the world to come...

31:25.092 --> 31:27.052
...but if he's stuck here
on this earth...

31:27.303 --> 31:31.056
...I know one thing that no man
wants to go through life without.

31:31.390 --> 31:32.558
What?

31:33.642 --> 31:34.685
Oh.

31:36.103 --> 31:37.730
That's a brilliant idea.

31:38.397 --> 31:40.482
Make like a <i>mohel,</i> huh?

31:40.774 --> 31:42.109
Finish his <i>bris.</i>

31:42.359 --> 31:43.527
Yeah.

31:45.696 --> 31:49.033
Paulie, get the ball cutters
from out of the truck.

31:49.533 --> 31:52.161
Ariel, we're going to plan B.

31:52.494 --> 31:54.914
The phone has been ringing
all morning.

31:55.164 --> 31:58.125
The Rotellis, the Trillos.
He has to do with computers.

31:58.375 --> 32:01.128
They're wonderful.
She invited us to brunch.

32:01.629 --> 32:03.464
- Really?
- Yep.

32:04.298 --> 32:07.551
But it was the food, Mainie.
Everybody raved about it.

32:07.760 --> 32:12.723
Cynthia said, "I love those rice balls,"
like she never had <i>arancini</i> before.

32:14.308 --> 32:17.102
Really, Mainie, I couldn't have
done it without you.

32:17.311 --> 32:19.605
It meant so much to me,
having you here.

32:19.813 --> 32:22.191
It just made it so much fun for me.

32:23.025 --> 32:26.153
Mainie, is something wrong?
You got something on your mind?

32:26.362 --> 32:27.738
What could be wrong?

32:29.031 --> 32:30.741
Listen, sweetie.

32:31.367 --> 32:35.663
It may not seem like it right now,
but you'll get back on your feet again.

32:36.413 --> 32:38.874
Carmela, I'm fine where I am.

32:40.125 --> 32:42.127
I know. That's not what I meant.

32:42.336 --> 32:45.464
Carmela, I never wanted
to tell you this.

32:46.340 --> 32:50.094
It happened so long ago.
You and Tony weren't even married.

32:50.678 --> 32:53.681
It's probably silly for me
to even bring it up now.

32:53.889 --> 32:55.182
What?

32:57.685 --> 32:59.728
You were at the shore
with your parents.

32:59.979 --> 33:02.481
You and Tony were on the outs.
He called me.

33:02.690 --> 33:03.774
He did?

33:03.983 --> 33:07.653
One thing led to another,
we started dating each other and...

33:08.570 --> 33:10.030
Carmela, I slept with him.

33:11.991 --> 33:13.701
You slept with Tony?

33:14.702 --> 33:17.204
Really, it wasn't for me.

33:17.746 --> 33:21.875
Carmela, what I'm trying to say is,
stop worrying about me.

33:22.126 --> 33:26.839
Really. I mean, we both made
our choices. I'm fine with mine.

33:45.566 --> 33:47.860
I'd like for you to consider this.

33:48.110 --> 33:49.153
Don't give me that.

33:49.403 --> 33:51.447
What's going on? Why'd you page me?

33:51.697 --> 33:54.241
This guy's trying to pull
some bullshit.

33:54.491 --> 33:57.244
Hey, ZZ Top. The guy gave you
the <i>get,</i> didn't he?

33:57.494 --> 34:01.415
But not because of you.
You threatened him with castration.

34:01.623 --> 34:06.628
It was business that brought him around.
He wanted 50%, you wanted 25%.

34:06.879 --> 34:09.381
So I split the difference.
I gave him 15%...

34:09.631 --> 34:12.259
...he gives my daughter
the divorce...

34:12.509 --> 34:16.055
- It's business. It worked out.
- You gotta walk with me, Shlomo.

34:16.305 --> 34:18.098
Listen, don't worry.

34:18.807 --> 34:21.435
I'm taking good care of you here.

34:21.643 --> 34:22.728
What's that?

34:22.978 --> 34:26.482
For your considerable trouble.
As the Talmud says...

34:27.649 --> 34:30.027
I don't give a shit
what he says, okay?

34:30.277 --> 34:33.530
You want to give your son-in-law
15% of the motel?

34:33.781 --> 34:36.241
You go ahead.
It comes out of your end.

34:36.533 --> 34:40.746
Now, we got you your <i>get.</i>
You get us our 25%. Got it?

34:40.996 --> 34:42.539
My son was right.

34:42.790 --> 34:45.834
You're mud. Godless clay!

34:47.169 --> 34:49.838
I created a living <i>golem!</i>

34:50.089 --> 34:51.507
What the fuck is a <i>golem?</i>

34:51.757 --> 34:53.801
It's a monster! Frankenstein!

34:54.051 --> 34:55.636
- Get out of here...
- Living dead!

34:55.886 --> 34:59.181
...before I take your asshole son
and shove him up your ass!

34:59.431 --> 35:00.849
Shut up!

35:12.486 --> 35:13.570
Hey.

35:14.863 --> 35:16.907
Hey, how you doing?

35:17.825 --> 35:19.201
One second.

35:22.287 --> 35:26.500
I got some good news. We're in the
motel business. How do you like that?

35:33.257 --> 35:34.466
Read this.

35:38.470 --> 35:40.264
102.7.

35:42.432 --> 35:44.935
They should take my temperature
with the other machine.

35:45.144 --> 35:47.521
Paulie broke his hand
on the guy's head.

35:47.729 --> 35:49.773
- Digital.
- We're waling on this guy.

35:50.023 --> 35:52.776
- I'm gonna cut his dick off.
- I'll call the nurse.

35:52.985 --> 35:56.071
He's mumbling and praying.
I'm getting his pants off.

35:56.280 --> 35:58.323
They should take my temperature again.

35:59.032 --> 36:00.826
Yeah, yeah, call them.

36:20.304 --> 36:21.763
Poor Jackie.

36:24.057 --> 36:26.310
God has his reasons.

36:26.727 --> 36:29.313
Livia, he looked twice as old as me.

36:29.521 --> 36:32.316
So, what's really on your mind,
Corrado?

36:32.858 --> 36:35.194
This Christopher Moltisanti.

36:35.402 --> 36:37.988
Christopher? What about him?

36:38.614 --> 36:40.991
Him and his little friend.

36:41.241 --> 36:45.078
They're slapping me in the face,
and they're hiding behind Tony.

36:45.287 --> 36:49.166
Well, Tony always loved Christopher
like a son.

36:49.666 --> 36:51.752
And so do I, Junior.

36:52.669 --> 36:55.047
He put up my storm windows for me
one year.

36:57.424 --> 36:58.675
Good.

37:05.349 --> 37:06.808
But what do I do?

37:07.059 --> 37:10.562
I just let him and this Filone kid
piss on me in public?

37:11.063 --> 37:14.233
And how far do I go before I light
a frigging match...

37:14.483 --> 37:17.027
...under that hotheaded son of yours?

37:18.695 --> 37:22.491
Maybe Christopher could use
a little talking to.

37:22.699 --> 37:24.117
You know.

37:24.910 --> 37:26.620
The other one...

37:27.412 --> 37:29.122
...Filone?

37:34.419 --> 37:35.879
I don't know.

37:42.135 --> 37:44.471
You got a lot of sense for an old gal.

37:44.930 --> 37:48.267
No, I'm a babbling idiot.

37:49.226 --> 37:52.646
That's why my son put me
in a nursing home.

37:55.065 --> 37:56.858
He didn't even care I was there.

37:58.902 --> 38:01.238
It was just him
and that fucking cancer.

38:05.701 --> 38:07.286
It's like he's already gone.

38:08.245 --> 38:09.579
Yes.

38:12.708 --> 38:13.959
Ah.

38:19.172 --> 38:21.049
Somebody called me
a Frankenstein today.

38:21.341 --> 38:22.384
Really?

38:22.634 --> 38:25.929
This Hasid I'm doing business with.

38:26.930 --> 38:29.683
These Hasids, I mean,
they're out there...

38:30.309 --> 38:32.686
...but they got their beliefs,
you know?

38:34.604 --> 38:37.524
They're not afraid of death.
This one guy wasn't.

38:37.774 --> 38:41.111
Maybe they have the belief
because they are afraid.

38:41.320 --> 38:42.946
I'm not afraid of death.

38:44.197 --> 38:47.617
Not if it's for something.

38:48.160 --> 38:50.871
You know? A war, something like that.

38:51.872 --> 38:53.373
A reason.

38:53.832 --> 38:55.000
But Jackie...

38:55.208 --> 38:58.378
To see this strong...

38:59.463 --> 39:00.881
...beautiful man...

39:03.133 --> 39:05.260
...just wither away to nothing...

39:09.306 --> 39:11.516
And you can't do nothing about it.

39:14.394 --> 39:15.896
You can't fight it.

39:17.022 --> 39:19.608
You envy the Hasids and their beliefs?

39:19.816 --> 39:21.735
All this shit's for nothing?

39:25.447 --> 39:28.241
If it's for nothing,
why must I think about it?

39:28.617 --> 39:30.702
That's the mystery, isn't it?

39:32.537 --> 39:36.333
The mystery of God,
or whatever you want to call it...

39:36.750 --> 39:39.878
...and why we're given
the questionable gift...

39:40.128 --> 39:42.506
...of knowing that we're gonna die.

39:51.139 --> 39:53.183
Do you feel like Frankenstein?

39:56.978 --> 39:58.230
A thing?

39:59.106 --> 40:01.149
Lacking humanity?

40:01.817 --> 40:04.111
Lacking human feelings?

40:37.769 --> 40:39.771
Thank you. That's for you.

40:40.021 --> 40:42.232
Say hello to Freddy, all right?

40:53.368 --> 40:54.828
Let go!

41:09.926 --> 41:11.178
Let me go!

41:11.386 --> 41:12.679
Let me go!

41:14.973 --> 41:17.184
You're friends of
Tony's <i>goomar,</i> right?

41:17.684 --> 41:19.603
Meadow wanted the crystal.

41:19.853 --> 41:23.231
If I didn't get it to her,
she would've went to Jefferson.

41:23.482 --> 41:26.443
You tell Tony.
They would've beat her and raped her!

41:26.693 --> 41:28.278
I don't want to die now!

41:29.196 --> 41:31.615
I didn't mean it. I am sorry!

41:31.823 --> 41:35.035
Listen to me!
I was trying to save her!

41:35.243 --> 41:37.287
Listen to me! You speak English?

41:37.537 --> 41:39.539
Don't shoot me! Don't shoot!

41:57.265 --> 41:58.767
Fuck!

42:59.035 --> 43:00.954
Hi, Jack. Bye, Jack.
